[
  // New York state-specific rule overrides.
  //
  // NY GILTI rate history has been consolidated into GILTI_INCLUSION_V1 in
  // default/gilti.json under JurisdictionRateOverrides["NY"]. No separate
  // NY rule is needed for rate-only changes — that was causing two rules to
  // match the same category/year and rely on Priority tie-breaking.
  //
  // Add entries here only for rules where NY requires a structurally different
  // formula (different input lines, different formula type) that cannot be
  // expressed as a rate override on the default rule.
  //
  // Example of when a separate rule IS warranted:
  //   NY_BONUS_DEPR_RECOVERY_V1 — 5-year recovery schedule is a code-based rule
  //   because it requires carry-forward state from prior years, which the
  //   LinearRate/PercentageOfLine formula types cannot express.
]
